values:
Right right... I said I was giving up writing...but I haven't.
I wrote a story last summer...and I just redid it a little...and I'd like to share.
I got a lot of negative critism on my last story...so I want to get some new critique.
Asides...I'll be bored out of my mind this summer...so what's a better bordem buster than writing slash???
Isn't that weird? But I realized it wasn't very good and I want to pursue my other intrests so I might come back eventually.

The stinkin power went off while I was trying to blog something on MySpace so I had to do it all over again. mychemicalslash took my story though! Yay! I need to catch up on the slash but I think I will fix my MySpace page first.
Well... Jenn gets to come over tomarrow! Yay! I'm gonna find out how to submit my story.

Well.... I woke up at 1. How pathetic. I think Jenn is coming over this weekend. How awesome. I've been lookinh at things on Wikipedia.com I found out Patrick Stumph is only 22. I found an awesome mesage board where ppl put MCR pictures and put captions on it. I think I'll go look at that now. I don't feel like reading slash.
Some chick on MySpace though my profile picture was me..... it was Gerard.

Well..... isn't it funny how I joined into the Coming Clean community and never read a single fic on there. Oh well. I'm just more of a gdslash.net type. If they'll ever come back up. Now I'm locked into the MCR slash. Well. Dunno. I have no one to talk to so that sort of sucks. I'm just sittin here chewing a pacifier.
I'm trying to write a Mikey/Gerard fic and I guess I can try and put it on MCR slash and the waycest community and the Gerard/Frank one too because it's got some of that.
I am now re-doing my Photobucket. It shall take forever. By the way.... it's PSAmericanLovers
Yeah.... I joined so I can comment on some stories on the MCR slash thing. Woot! Ok......
Ok coming clean has wayyyyyyy too many fanfics to deal with. I would love to read them but its too much trouble to go into every single one and find the summery.
There, I fixed my LJ up now. It's a little bit prettier.

Well atlest my mom dosn't know about LiveJournal yet. I told her I has a Xanga: http://www.xanga.com/green_children and a MySpace which I forgot. But now I have a LiveJournal. I think I shall like it here. Yay, yet another website I'm a noob on.
